  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Through FY2026 to date, federal contract obligations for NAICS 541519 total $13.1B across 20,091 awards with an average award size of $654K. Obligations are down 47.1% year over year, and current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date). Historical annual obligations show a peak range from $22.4B to $25.4B in FY21–FY25, followed by the FY26 to date total of $13.1B. The Top 10 buying agencies for FY2026 to date include the Department of Defense at $3.4B, the Department of Veterans Affairs at $1.8B, and the Department of Homeland Security at $1.3B. Leading vendors for FY2026 to date include THUNDERCAT TECHNOLOGY, LLC at $649M, FOUR POINTS TECHNOLOGY, L.L.C. at $633M, and V3GATE, LLC at $551M. The dataset reflects both concentration among a handful of large buyers and vendors and a substantial year-over-year decline in obligations through the current fiscal year to date.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "What does the FY2026 to date obligation total indicate about market size?",
        "body": "The market reached $13.1B in obligations through FY2026 to date. That total is down 47.1% year over year and follows annual obligations of $22.4B, $23.4B, $25.4B, $25.3B, and $24.9B in FY21–FY25. The current-year total is partial (fiscal year to date) and reflects fewer obligations compared with prior full fiscal years."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Who are the largest buyers and contractors in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The largest buying agencies through FY2026 to date are the Department of Defense at $3.4B, the Department of Veterans Affairs at $1.8B, and the Department of Homeland Security at $1.3B. The top vendors for the same period are THUNDERCAT TECHNOLOGY, LLC at $649M, FOUR POINTS TECHNOLOGY, L.L.C. at $633M, and V3GATE, LLC at $551M."
      }
    ]
